{"id": "nsci-phosphorus-element-065", "type": "fact", "statement": "Phosphorus is a chemical element with symbol P and atomic number 15, essential for DNA and discovered by an alchemist searching for gold.", "explanation": "Phosphorus was discovered in 1669 by Hennig Brand, who isolated it from urine while trying to create the philosopher's stone. White phosphorus glows in the dark (the word phosphorus means 'light-bearer' in Greek). It is essential for life — DNA, RNA, and ATP all contain phosphorus.", "wowFactor": "An alchemist discovered phosphorus by boiling 1,500 gallons of urine looking for gold!", "quizQuestion": "How was phosphorus originally discovered?", "correctAnswer": "Isolated from urine by an alchemist", "distractors": [{"text": "Mined from volcanic rock", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Extracted from seawater", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Found in meteorites", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Synthesized in a lab", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Distilled from bone ash", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Discovered in soil samples", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Isolated from plant matter", "difficultyTier": "medium"}], "variants": [{"question": "What does 'phosphorus' mean in Greek?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Light-bearer", "distractors": ["Fire-maker", "Gold-seeker", "Star-dust"]}, {"question": "Which element is essential for DNA, RNA, and ATP?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Phosphorus", "distractors": ["Potassium", "Sodium", "Calcium"]}, {"question": "Phosphorus is NOT found in which biological molecule?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Hemoglobin", "distractors": ["DNA", "RNA", "ATP"]}, {"question": "White phosphorus _____ in the dark.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Glows", "distractors": ["Freezes", "Evaporates", "Hardens"]}, {"question": "Phosphorus was discovered by an alchemist trying to make gold.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["Fal