{"id": "nsci-lanthanum-element-067", "type": "fact", "statement": "Lanthanum is a chemical element with symbol La and atomic number 57, the first of the lanthanide series.", "explanation": "Lanthanum's name comes from the Greek 'lanthanein' meaning 'to lie hidden,' because it was concealed within cerium ore for decades before discovery. It gives the entire lanthanide group its name. Lanthanum is used in camera and telescope lenses, and in hybrid car batteries.", "wowFactor": "Lanthanum literally means 'hidden one' — it hid inside another element for years!", "quizQuestion": "What does the name lanthanum mean in Greek?", "correctAnswer": "To lie hidden", "distractors": [{"text": "To shine brightly", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "First born", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Earth metal", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Rare one", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Strong light", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Heavy stone", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Moon metal", "difficultyTier": "easy"}], "variants": [{"question": "Which group of elements is named after lanthanum?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Lanthanides", "distractors": ["Actinides", "Halogens", "Noble gases"]}, {"question": "Lanthanum is used in which type of car batteries?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Hybrid car batteries", "distractors": ["Lead-acid batteries", "Alkaline batteries", "Zinc-air batteries"]}, {"question": "Lanthanum is NOT used in which product?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Steel alloys", "distractors": ["Camera lenses", "Telescope lenses", "Hybrid batteries"]}, {"question": "Lanthanum is the first element in the _____ series.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Lanthanide", "distractors": ["Actinide", "Halogen", "Alkaline"]}, {"question": "Lanthanum was discovered hidden within cerium ore.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 3, "funScore": 6, "visualDescription": "A pix