{"id": "nsci-chlorine-element-068", "type": "fact", "statement": "Chlorine is a chemical element with symbol Cl and atomic number 17, a yellow-green toxic gas essential for water purification.", "explanation": "Chlorine was first used to purify drinking water in 1897, revolutionizing public health by virtually eliminating waterborne diseases like cholera and typhoid. Its name comes from the Greek 'chloros' meaning yellow-green. Chlorine is also used in PVC plastics, bleach, and swimming pool disinfection.", "wowFactor": "Chlorinating water is considered one of the greatest public health advances in history!", "quizQuestion": "What does 'chlorine' mean in Greek?", "correctAnswer": "Yellow-green", "distractors": [{"text": "Poisonous", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Sharp smell", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Clean water", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Bitter taste", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Strong gas", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Pale light", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Pure element", "difficultyTier": "easy"}], "variants": [{"question": "When was chlorine first used to purify drinking water?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "1897", "distractors": ["1850", "1920", "1776"]}, {"question": "Which diseases did chlorinated water help eliminate?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Cholera and typhoid", "distractors": ["Malaria and dengue", "Smallpox and measles", "Influenza and polio"]}, {"question": "Chlorine is NOT used in which product?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Fertilizer", "distractors": ["PVC plastics", "Bleach", "Swimming pool disinfectant"]}, {"question": "Chlorine is a _____ gas at room temperature.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Yellow-green", "distractors": ["Colorless", "Blue", "Red"]}, {"question": "Chlorine is used to purify drinking water.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 2, "funScore": 7, "visualDescription": "A 