{"id": "nsci-carbon-element-069", "type": "fact", "statement": "Carbon is a chemical element with symbol C and atomic number 6, the basis of all known life and capable of forming more compounds than any other element.", "explanation": "Carbon can form four bonds with other atoms, giving it unmatched versatility. It exists as diamond (the hardest natural material), graphite (one of the softest), graphene (the strongest material ever tested), and fullerenes (soccer-ball-shaped molecules). All known life is carbon-based.", "wowFactor": "Carbon forms the hardest AND one of the softest natural materials — diamond and graphite!", "quizQuestion": "How many bonds can a carbon atom typically form?", "correctAnswer": "4", "distractors": [{"text": "3", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "2", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "6", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "5", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "1", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "8", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "7", "difficultyTier": "easy"}], "variants": [{"question": "Which carbon allotrope is the hardest natural material?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Diamond", "distractors": ["Graphene", "Fullerene", "Graphite"]}, {"question": "What is the strongest material ever tested?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Graphene", "distractors": ["Diamond", "Carbon nanotube", "Steel"]}, {"question": "Which is NOT an allotrope of carbon?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Quartz", "distractors": ["Diamond", "Graphite", "Fullerene"]}, {"question": "All known life on Earth is _____-based.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Carbon", "distractors": ["Silicon", "Nitrogen", "Oxygen"]}, {"question": "Carbon can form more compounds than any other element.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 1, "funScore": 9, "visualDescription": "A pixel art split scene: a brilliant diamond on the left transforming into soft graphite pencil on the right