{"id": "nsci-nitrogen-element-070", "type": "fact", "statement": "Nitrogen is a chemical element with symbol N and atomic number 7, making up 78% of Earth's atmosphere.", "explanation": "Nitrogen is the most abundant gas in our atmosphere but is largely inert due to its strong triple bond. The Haber-Bosch process, which converts atmospheric nitrogen into ammonia for fertilizer, is considered one of the most important inventions in history — it feeds roughly half the world's population.", "wowFactor": "The Haber-Bosch process for making nitrogen fertilizer feeds half of all humans alive today!", "quizQuestion": "What percentage of Earth's atmosphere is nitrogen?", "correctAnswer": "78%", "distractors": [{"text": "21%", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "68%", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "88%", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "50%", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "95%", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "45%", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "72%", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "Which process converts atmospheric nitrogen into fertilizer?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Haber-Bosch process", "distractors": ["Bessemer process", "Fischer-Tropsch process", "Ostwald process"]}, {"question": "What type of bond makes nitrogen gas so stable?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Triple bond", "distractors": ["Double bond", "Single bond", "Ionic bond"]}, {"question": "Nitrogen is NOT the most abundant gas in which atmosphere?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Mars", "distractors": ["Earth", "Titan", "Triton"]}, {"question": "Nitrogen makes up _____% of Earth's atmosphere.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "78", "distractors": ["21", "68", "50"]}, {"question": "The Haber-Bosch process helps feed about half the world's population.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 2, "funScore": 8, "visualDescription": "A pixel art pie chart of Earth's atmosphere with