{"id": "nsci-lutetium-element-071", "type": "fact", "statement": "Lutetium is a chemical element with symbol Lu and atomic number 71, the last and heaviest of the lanthanide series.", "explanation": "Lutetium is named after Lutetia, the ancient Roman name for Paris. It is the hardest and densest lanthanide element. Lutetium-176 is used in radiometric dating of meteorites to determine the age of the solar system, and lutetium compounds are used in cancer treatment.", "wowFactor": "Scientists use lutetium atoms in meteorites to figure out how old the solar system is!", "quizQuestion": "What city is lutetium named after?", "correctAnswer": "Paris", "distractors": [{"text": "London", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Lyon", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Lucerne", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Lisbon", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Luxembourg", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Leipzig", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Lausanne", "difficultyTier": "medium"}], "variants": [{"question": "What is lutetium used for in geology?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Radiometric dating of meteorites", "distractors": ["Mineral identification", "Soil analysis", "Rock hardness testing"]}, {"question": "Which lanthanide element is the heaviest?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Lutetium", "distractors": ["Lanthanum", "Cerium", "Ytterbium"]}, {"question": "Lutetium is NOT used in which field?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Food science", "distractors": ["Cancer treatment", "Meteorite dating", "PET scanning"]}, {"question": "Lutetium is named after Lutetia, the Roman name for _____.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Paris", "distractors": ["London", "Lyon", "Lisbon"]}, {"question": "Lutetium is the heaviest lanthanide element.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 4, "funScore": 7, "visualDescription": "A pixel art Eiffel Tower with a glowing periodic table element floating