{"id": "nsci-sulfur-element-073", "type": "fact", "statement": "Sulfur is a chemical element with symbol S and atomic number 16, known since antiquity as 'brimstone.'", "explanation": "Sulfur is mentioned in the Bible as brimstone and has been used since ancient times. It is essential for life — found in the amino acids cysteine and methionine. Sulfur is bright yellow in its solid form and produces a distinctive rotten-egg smell as hydrogen sulfide. Volcanic hot springs often contain dissolved sulfur.", "wowFactor": "The 'fire and brimstone' in ancient texts was literally sulfur burning with a blue flame!", "quizQuestion": "What is the ancient name for sulfur?", "correctAnswer": "Brimstone", "distractors": [{"text": "Quicksilver", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Fool's gold", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Black powder", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Saltpeter", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Cinnabar", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Vitriol", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Antimony", "difficultyTier": "medium"}], "variants": [{"question": "What color is solid sulfur?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Yellow", "distractors": ["White", "Red", "Gray"]}, {"question": "Which gas gives rotten eggs their smell?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Hydrogen sulfide", "distractors": ["Sulfur dioxide", "Ammonia", "Methane"]}, {"question": "Sulfur is NOT found in which amino acid?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Glycine", "distractors": ["Cysteine", "Methionine", "Taurine"]}, {"question": "Sulfur burns with a _____ flame.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Blue", "distractors": ["Red", "Yellow", "Green"]}, {"question": "Sulfur was known in ancient times as brimstone.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 2, "funScore": 8, "visualDescription": "A pixel art volcanic hot spring with bright yellow sulfur deposits around its edges. Blue sulfur flames flicker at the surf