{"id": "nsci-palladium-element-074", "type": "fact", "statement": "Palladium is a chemical element with symbol Pd and atomic number 46, a platinum-group metal crucial for catalytic converters.", "explanation": "Palladium was named after the asteroid Pallas, which itself was named after the Greek goddess Athena. About 85% of palladium ends up in catalytic converters in car exhaust systems, where it converts toxic pollutants into less harmful substances. It is also used in electronics, dentistry, and hydrogen purification.", "wowFactor": "Palladium in your car's exhaust system converts poisonous gases into water and carbon dioxide!", "quizQuestion": "What is the primary use of palladium?", "correctAnswer": "Catalytic converters in cars", "distractors": [{"text": "Jewelry making", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Nuclear reactors", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Computer chips", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Solar panels", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Battery production", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Paint pigments", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Medical implants", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "What is palladium named after?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "The asteroid Pallas", "distractors": ["A Greek temple", "A Roman city", "A scientist"]}, {"question": "What percentage of palladium is used in catalytic converters?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "About 85%", "distractors": ["About 50%", "About 30%", "About 95%"]}, {"question": "Palladium is NOT used in which application?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Food preservation", "distractors": ["Catalytic converters", "Dentistry", "Hydrogen purification"]}, {"question": "Palladium converts toxic car exhaust into less _____ substances.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Harmful", "distractors": ["Dense", "Volatile", "Visible"]}, {"question": "Palladium belongs to the platinum group of metals.", "type": "true_false", "correctA