{"id": "nsci-hassium-element-077", "type": "fact", "statement": "Hassium is a synthetic element with symbol Hs and atomic number 108, named after the German state of Hesse.", "explanation": "Hassium was first synthesized in 1978 at the GSI Helmholtz Centre in Darmstadt, Germany. Named after the Latin 'Hassia' for Hesse, it is produced by bombarding lead with iron ions. Only a handful of atoms have ever been created, each lasting just seconds before decaying.", "wowFactor": "Only a few atoms of hassium have ever existed — each one vanishes in seconds!", "quizQuestion": "What is hassium named after?", "correctAnswer": "The German state of Hesse", "distractors": [{"text": "A German scientist", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "The city of Hamburg", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "A Latin word for heavy", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "A mountain range", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "The Haber process", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "A Greek word", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "The Hassium river", "difficultyTier": "hard"}], "variants": [{"question": "What is the atomic number of hassium?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "108", "distractors": ["107", "109", "110"]}, {"question": "How is hassium produced?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Bombarding lead with iron ions", "distractors": ["Bombarding gold with protons", "Nuclear fission", "Natural decay"]}, {"question": "Hassium is NOT which type of element?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Stable", "distractors": ["Synthetic", "Radioactive", "Transactinide"]}, {"question": "Hassium was first synthesized in _____.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "1978", "distractors": ["1988", "1968", "1998"]}, {"question": "Hassium atoms exist for only seconds before decaying.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 5, "funScore": 6, "visualDescription": "A pixel art particle accelerator chamber with iron beams colliding with