{"id": "nsci-rhodium-element-078", "type": "fact", "statement": "Rhodium is a chemical element with symbol Rh and atomic number 45, the most expensive precious metal commonly traded.", "explanation": "Rhodium is extremely rare — about 30 tonnes are mined annually worldwide. Its name comes from the Greek 'rhodon' meaning rose, due to the rose-red color of its compounds. Rhodium is used to coat white gold jewelry and in catalytic converters. It reached a record price of over $29,000 per ounce in 2021.", "wowFactor": "Rhodium once cost $29,000 per ounce — more than 15 times the price of gold!", "quizQuestion": "What does 'rhodium' mean in Greek?", "correctAnswer": "Rose", "distractors": [{"text": "Silver", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Rare", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Red", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Bright", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Heavy", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Shiny", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Noble", "difficultyTier": "medium"}], "variants": [{"question": "What is rhodium used for in jewelry?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Coating white gold", "distractors": ["Making rings", "Setting diamonds", "Coloring gems"]}, {"question": "Which precious metal reached over $29,000/oz in 2021?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "Rhodium", "distractors": ["Platinum", "Gold", "Palladium"]}, {"question": "Rhodium is NOT used in which application?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Coins", "distractors": ["Catalytic converters", "White gold plating", "Laboratory equipment"]}, {"question": "About _____ tonnes of rhodium are mined annually.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "30", "distractors": ["300", "3", "3000"]}, {"question": "Rhodium's name comes from the Greek word for rose.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 3, "funScore": 8, "visualDescription": "A pixel art jewelry display with gleaming rhodium-plated rings. A price chart shows a d