{"id": "nsci-molar-gas-constant-081", "type": "fact", "statement": "The molar gas constant R equals approximately 8.314 J/(mol·K) and connects energy, temperature, and the amount of substance in gas laws.", "explanation": "The molar gas constant appears in the ideal gas law PV = nRT, connecting pressure, volume, temperature, and amount of gas. It is the product of Avogadro's number and Boltzmann's constant. R appears throughout chemistry and physics wherever gases and thermodynamics meet.", "wowFactor": "One simple constant R ties together pressure, volume, temperature, and amount in a single elegant equation!", "quizQuestion": "In the ideal gas law PV = nRT, what does R represent?", "correctAnswer": "The molar gas constant", "distractors": [{"text": "The reaction rate", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "The resistance", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "The radius", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Boltzmann's constant", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "The Rydberg constant", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "The universal constant", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "The entropy factor", "difficultyTier": "medium"}], "variants": [{"question": "What is the approximate value of the molar gas constant?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "8.314 J/(mol·K)", "distractors": ["6.626 J·s", "1.381 J/K", "9.807 m/s²"]}, {"question": "Which equation features the molar gas constant?", "type": "reverse", "correctAnswer": "PV = nRT", "distractors": ["E = mc²", "F = ma", "V = IR"]}, {"question": "The molar gas constant does NOT appear in which law?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Ohm's law", "distractors": ["Ideal gas law", "Clausius-Clapeyron equation", "Nernst equation"]}, {"question": "R is the product of Avogadro's number and _____ constant.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Boltzmann's", "distractors": ["Planck's", "Faraday's", "Hubble's"]}, {"question": "The molar gas constant has units of energy per mole per kelvin.", "type": "true_f