{"id": "nsci-neutron-mass-083", "type": "fact", "statement": "The neutron has a rest mass of approximately 1.675 × 10⁻²⁷ kg, slightly heavier than a proton.", "explanation": "A neutron is about 0.14% heavier than a proton. This tiny mass difference is crucial — if neutrons were lighter than protons, protons would decay and atoms as we know them couldn't exist. Free neutrons are unstable and decay into a proton, electron, and antineutrino with a half-life of about 10 minutes.", "wowFactor": "If the neutron were just slightly lighter, all atoms would fall apart and the universe couldn't exist!", "quizQuestion": "How does a neutron's mass compare to a proton's?", "correctAnswer": "Slightly heavier", "distractors": [{"text": "Exactly the same", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Slightly lighter", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Twice as heavy", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Half as heavy", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Much heavier", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "10% heavier", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Depends on the isotope", "difficultyTier": "medium"}], "variants": [{"question": "What is the half-life of a free neutron?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "About 10 minutes", "distractors": ["About 1 second", "About 1 hour", "About 1 day"]}, {"question": "What does a free neutron decay into?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Proton, electron, and antineutrino", "distractors": ["Two photons", "Quark soup", "Hydrogen atom"]}, {"question": "A neutron is NOT made up of which quark combination?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Two up quarks and one down quark", "distractors": ["Two down quarks and one up quark", "Three quarks total", "Quarks held by gluons"]}, {"question": "Free neutrons are _____ particles.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Unstable", "distractors": ["Stable", "Charged", "Massless"]}, {"question": "A neutron is slightly heavier than a proton.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 3, "funScore": 7, "visualDescription": "A pixel art neutron rendered as a blue sphere with two down quarks and one up quark visible inside, connected by gluon springs. A decay diagram shows it splitting into a proton, electron, and ghostly antineutrino.", "ageRating": "teen", "category": "natural_sciences", "contentType": "knowledge", "rarity": "uncommon", "sourceName": "Wikidata", "sourceUrl": "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q98000454", "sourceRecordId": "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q98000454", "tags": ["neutron", "physics", "particle-physics", "mass", "nuclear"]}
{"id": "nsci-latex-material-084", "type": "fact", "statement": "Latex is a stable dispersion of polymer microparticles in water, naturally produced by over 20,000 plant species as a defense mechanism.", "explanation": "Natural latex comes primarily from the rubber tree (Hevea brasiliensis) and is harvested by making incisions in the bark. Plants evolved latex as a defense — its sticky consistency traps insects and seals wounds. Synthetic latex is made from petroleum-based monomers and is used in paints, coatings, and adhesives.", "wowFactor": "Over 20,000 plant species make latex — it's basically plant blood that traps bugs!", "quizQuestion": "Why do plants produce latex?", "correctAnswer": "As a defense mechanism against insects and wounds", "distractors": [{"text": "To attract pollinators", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "For photosynthesis", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "To store nutrients", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "To absorb water", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "To communicate with other plants", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "For seed dispersal", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "To regulate temperature", "difficultyTier": "easy"}], "variants": [{"question": "Which tree is the primary source of natural rubber latex?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Hevea brasiliensis (rubber tree)", "distractors": ["Oak tree", "Pine tree", "Maple tree"]}, {"question": "How many plant species produce latex?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Over 20,000", "distractors": ["About 100", "About 1,000", "About 500"]}, {"question": "Latex is NOT used in which product?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Glass manufacturing", "distractors": ["Gloves", "Paint", "Adhesives"]}, {"question": "Latex is harvested from rubber trees by making _____ in the bark.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Incisions", "distractors": ["Holes", "Burns", "Grafts"]}, {"question": "Natural latex is a plant-produced substance.", "type": "true_f