{"id": "nsci-gold-powder-093", "type": "fact", "statement": "Gold powder is finely divided gold used as a pigment, in electronics, and in decorative arts since ancient times.", "explanation": "Gold powder has been used in art and decoration for millennia. In Japanese art, it is sprinkled on lacquer to create maki-e designs. Modern gold powder is used in electronics (gold paste for circuit printing), dentistry, and even as a food decoration (edible gold leaf). Gold nanoparticles appear red or purple rather than gold-colored.", "wowFactor": "Tiny gold particles aren't gold-colored at all — they appear red or purple!", "quizQuestion": "What color do gold nanoparticles appear?", "correctAnswer": "Red or purple", "distractors": [{"text": "Gold", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Silver", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Blue", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "Green", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "White", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "Orange", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "Black", "difficultyTier": "easy"}], "variants": [{"question": "What Japanese art technique uses gold powder on lacquer?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Maki-e", "distractors": ["Kintsugi", "Shibori", "Ukiyo-e"]}, {"question": "Gold powder is used in which modern technology?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "Electronics circuit printing", "distractors": ["Nuclear reactors", "Solar panels", "Battery anodes"]}, {"question": "Gold powder is NOT used in which field?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Structural engineering", "distractors": ["Electronics", "Dentistry", "Food decoration"]}, {"question": "Gold in nanoparticle form changes _____ compared to bulk gold.", "type": "fill_blank", "correctAnswer": "Color", "distractors": ["Weight", "Conductivity", "Melting point"]}, {"question": "Edible gold leaf is safe for human consumption.", "type": "true_false", "correctAnswer": "True", "distractors": ["False"]}], "difficulty": 3, "funScore": 8, "visualDescri