{"id": "nsci-banana-leaf-095", "type": "fact", "statement": "Banana leaves are used as natural plates, cooking wrappers, and packaging across tropical cultures, serving over 500 million people daily.", "explanation": "Banana leaves are waterproof, flexible, and large enough to serve as plates and food wrappers across South and Southeast Asia, Africa, and Latin America. They add a subtle flavor when used to wrap food for steaming or grilling. Unlike paper or plastic, banana leaves are fully biodegradable and require no energy to manufacture.", "wowFactor": "Banana leaves serve as plates for over 500 million people — the world's biggest zero-waste dining!", "quizQuestion": "What makes banana leaves ideal as natural plates?", "correctAnswer": "They are waterproof, flexible, and large", "distractors": [{"text": "They are nutritious to eat", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "They kill bacteria", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "They are transparent", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "They stay frozen easily", "difficultyTier": "easy"}, {"text": "They absorb heat", "difficultyTier": "medium"}, {"text": "They change color when food is bad", "difficultyTier": "hard"}, {"text": "They are fireproof", "difficultyTier": "easy"}], "variants": [{"question": "In which regions are banana leaves commonly used as plates?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "South and Southeast Asia, Africa, Latin America", "distractors": ["Europe and North America", "Antarctica", "Arctic regions"]}, {"question": "What happens when food is wrapped in banana leaves for cooking?", "type": "forward", "correctAnswer": "The leaves add a subtle flavor", "distractors": ["The food cooks faster", "The leaves dissolve", "The food turns green"]}, {"question": "Banana leaves are NOT used for which purpose?", "type": "negative", "correctAnswer": "Building permanent structures", "distractors": ["Serving food", "Wrapping for cooking", "Biodegradable packaging"]}, {"question": "Banana leaves are fully